    <div class="content">
        <h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>Besouhola CRM API (Laravel + Sanctum + Multi-tenant)</p>
<aside>
    <strong>Base URL</strong>: <code>http://127.0.0.1:8000</code>
</aside>
<p>This documentation describes the API contract for Besouhola CRM.</p>
<h3 id="authentication">Authentication</h3>
<p>Most endpoints require a Sanctum token:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code></li>
</ul>
<p>You can obtain a token via the login endpoint (<code>POST /api/auth/login</code> or <code>POST /api/login</code>).</p>
<h3 id="tenant-context">Tenant context</h3>
<p>This is a multi-tenant system. For mobile clients, the recommended approach is to send the tenant slug on every request:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>X-Tenant-Id: &lt;tenant-slug&gt;</code></li>
</ul>
<p>The backend also supports <code>X-Tenant</code> as an alias.</p>

        <h1 id="authenticating-requests">Authenticating requests</h1>
<p>To authenticate requests, include an <strong><code>Authorization</code></strong> header with the value <strong><code>"Bearer {BEARER_TOKEN}"</code></strong>.</p>
<p>All authenticated endpoints are marked with a <code>requires authentication</code> badge in the documentation below.</p>
<p>Get a token by calling <code>POST /api/auth/login</code> (tenant) or <code>POST /api/login</code> (central), then send it as <code>Authorization: Bearer ...</code>. For tenant-scoped requests, also send <code>X-Tenant-Id</code>.</p>

        <h1 id="endpoints">Endpoints</h1>

    

